Ordering note: the publications page groups entries by the `year` string and
sorts groups in descending lexicographic order (verified in jekyll-scholar
7.2.2). ASCII gives lowercase > uppercase > digits, so groups render
top-to-bottom in that order (e.g. forthcoming, Submitted, In Preparation,
2026, 2023, 2021 would sort that way). Keep casing consistent with how you
want groups labeled; headers are displayed uppercase via CSS.

Add your own publications below using BibTeX format, e.g.:

@article{yourkey_2026,
  author  = {Lastname, Firstname},
  title   = {Your Paper Title},
  journal = {Journal Name},
  volume  = {1},
  number  = {1},
  pages   = {1--10},
  year    = {2026},
  doi     = {10.xxxx/xxxxx},
  html    = {https://example.com/paper}
}

Note: the entry above is a real, valid @article{} entry, so it WILL show up
on your publications page as a placeholder. Replace its fields with your own
real publication, or delete the whole @article{...} block once you've added
your own entries.
